# Commit Style Reference

- Follow repository commit style from `docs/08-commit-conventions.md`.
- Use `<type>: <short message in lower case>`.
- Keep subject concise and without trailing period.
- Add optional body when why/context is non-obvious.
- Prefer accurate type selection (`feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`, `build`, `perf`, `style`).
